===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|when|when(ne)}}, {{m|enm|whan|whan(ne)}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hwenne}}, {{m|ang|hwænne}}, {{m|ang|hwonne||when}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hwannē||at what time, when}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*kʷis||interrogative base}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|wanneer||when}} and {{m|nl|wen||when, if}}, {{cog|nds|wannehr||when}}, {{m|nds|wann||when}} and {{m|nds|wenn||if, when}}, {{cog|de|wann||when}} and {{m|de|wenn||when, if}}, {{cog|got|𐍈𐌰𐌽||when, how}}, {{cog|la|quandō||when}}. More at {{l|en|who}}.

Interjection sense: a playful misunderstanding of "say when" (i.e. say when you want me to stop) as "say [the word] ''when''".

